description:
The album Astral Traveling by Innerspace Halflife is among us with 9 tunes straight from the universal psyche, yet articulated with the tools of human perception through waveforms. Deeper and deeper the tunes take a listener on a journey of spacey pads, longing melodies, electronic bass notes, and jacking drum programming.

In terms of human understanding, the universe is infinite which makes any scenario one can think of possible. With this in mind, Astral Traveling was composed and explores the deepness of creativity as Innerspace Halflife reaches down to pull out sounds using various techniques.

a1.Teardrop from Teardrop from Nebula 1122+22
a2.Particle Burst
b1.Breaking Lights
b2.Ionic Transport
c1.Starfields
c2.Galaxy Dreaming
d1.Acid Dust
d2.Escape System

Distributed by Crosstalk International

description:
Murph Tone Jack Session Remixes have come up, I was planning to do a remix vinyl for at least a year. And finally the opportunity came up for me to get four reinterpretations from Chicago producers Chicago Skyway, G. Marcell, Ike Release, and Steven Tang. Their contributions expand the Jack Session with deep and rhythmic tunes that will rock from warehouse to boats.

Murph Tone Jack Session Remixes

a1. Chicago Head - Chicago Skyway Remix
a2. Tender B - G. Marcell Tender Touch Remix
b1. Technicals - Ike Release Remix
b2. Tender B - Steven Tang Remix

Synapsis-009
Distributed by Crosstalk

description:
I am catalogue number 016 on Synapsis Records. Four tunes called 4D Mind Sculpting comprise this 12” that fill up the frequency spectrum with its acid lines, chord progressions, and arpeggiation lines. Four dimensions do not exist in our reality but if one could imagine the extra dimensional sense, then these four compositions are what I imagine. 

Distributed by DBH.

a1. Arp Love Confusion
a2. Leecher

b2.Sensei

description:
Lyon, France, the city of lights materializes 016. Slowmotion is born from a collaboration between myself and Vince Noog. Noog has been rocking more on the Techno tip over the years with releases on his label, but when the collaboration took place beat down feels appeared; causing some house jams to develop. The EP is called Beats from Lugdunum, but why? Lugdunum is the old school name for Lyon and the surrounding areas, and these tunes were conceptualized, composed, and beated right there.

a.Affaire de Famille
b1.Évasion Urbaine
b2.Le Grand Saut

Written, arranged, and produced by Hakim Murphy and Vince Noog.

mdreams016

Interview:

1.beunderground.ro: Vinil or Digital?

Hakim Murphy: For my musical purposes I use all formats available to me as technology is here to help me present music. Now when I dj I prefer to play vinyl but when on tour I have to bring cds for weight purposes, plus I like to try unreleased music to see how it works on the dance floor.

2.beunderground.ro: If vinil, why you consider that vinyl it's superior?

Hakim Murphy: I like vinyl more because of the feel of actually playing records. I also think the sound quality is a warmer, plus there is quality control with vinyl as some people burn mp3s of youtube which sonically sound horrible most of the time.

3.beunderground.ro: We know that you was a dancer, still love to dance?

Hakim Murphy: Yeah, I still like to dance as I have been practicing more lately, so that is something I will always do as much as possible.

4.beunderground.ro: How you started to play music?

Hakim Murphy: Basically I got tired of hearing djs playing the same records over and over again at parties, so I began djing, and then I moved into production. Probably a natural calling for me, since I have always been interested in music.

5.beunderground.ro: Where is your favorite place to play music? and why?

Hakim Murphy: This is a hard question to answer, I guess I do not have a favorite place to play, I just like to play whenever I get a chance.

6.beunderground.ro: What do you stay with production, some new ep?

Hakim Murphy: I make music to help with my mental state as I use it for meditation and therapy purposes. New EPs coming soon are Darkness EP on Sound Black, Examplars EP on Machining Dreams, Astrodynamics EP with Ike Release as Innerspace Halflife on Episodes materializing within the next month of so.

7.beunderground.ro: In june you played in Romania, how it was for you?

Hakim Murphy: Romania was really special party for me, it was my first international gig and I enjoyed the crowd and the people immensely. I enjoyed learning about the culture of Romania and meeting so many nice people. 

8.beunderground.ro: Some words about your record for beunderground.ro.

Hakim Murphy: As per my usual podcast flow, I just got a bunch of new records from friends, associates, and distributors; along with some of my releases, so put down a mix of these tunes that I was feeling at the time.

9.beunderground.ro: If should characterize your style with spices, that would be?

Hakim Murphy: Chilli pepper because of the music selection, and sugar because of the long blends.

10.beunderground.ro: At least, some words for your fans from Romania?

Hakim Murphy: Enjoy the mix, and hopefully I will be back soon to share some good music with you all again. Also check out the Chameleon parties jumping off in Bucharest, the locals djs are playing some nice music... Much love Romania.

description:
For this weeks Podcast number 61, we've got Hakim Murphy mixin' it up for us. His set includes a couple of older tunes mixed in with a few from Hakim himself. Having rarely played these in clubs, he finds it refreshing when he has the opportunity to create a podcast and listen back to it many times. Murphy's next up coming release will be with Synapsis Records, not a doubt they'll be something special.

Thanks a lot to Hakim Murphy for creating this week Podcast number 61, exclusively for Solenoid Radio.

"Illustration by Tara Deacon"

description:
Let's high up the frequency of Uploadings - so this means here it comes - already: 
Episode 3 of Aufschnitt.

Thank you Hakim Murphy for your Mixtape, that I'm finally able to present in this series of mixes bound together as "Aufschnitt"!
I chose this guy, because years ago, when I was still digging without any plan, Hakim seemed to be the first man, with a special manner to produce to me -
it's what I made of his EP : Spectrum Print.

Tickeling electronic sounds, coming from a deep that calls from far away and whcih you really can here in some Lo-Fi feelings.
Also this mix keeps some of these mysterious and soft vibes which we bring to you at home, to fall down into dizzyness after these sunny days.

Enjoy the journey into a memory of Soul, R'n'B and Jazz

Y'all have a good time - thank you for enjoying this!!

Robert

description: This remix was original done back in 2006, but the label had a last minute change of heart and it never got used. Since then, it been the subject of a lot of chatter and mail traffic with people trying to get hold of a copy. I dug it out late last year with a view to putting it in my sets, but on reflection it felt a little on the lightweight side .... so I took the turbo-charger to it & flame-grilled it to woppa-size for my own DJ sets.
title: Black Twang - Travellin' (Elite Force Remix) [2006]

description:
Download the #maxi2012 including this track at http://www.mediafire.com/?sbem6mby5964jws

In his unstoppable up and coming career in the US market , the music producer/dj Brainiac Beats, also known in the Spanish scene as El Cerebro, has cooked up a solid maxi single that includes 6 artists from NYC:

• Joell Ortiz, from Slaughterhouse, recently signed by Eminem to Shady Records.
• AG, from the legendary supergroup Diggin In The Crates (DITC) formed also by Big L, Fat Joe, Big Pun, O.C., Diamond D, Lord Finesse, Buckwild & Showbiz.
• Shea Davis, BLAM DVDs’ creator, who recently released a mixtape with Dj Kay Slay.
• Dwayne Collins, R&B singer who has collaborated with Styles P, Emilio Rojas, etc.
• Nikal Fieldz, who has worked with Marley Marl & KRS-ONE among others.
• Praise, who has recorded with JR Writer, Noah Jones, etc.

All of these artists pair up in 3 different tracks downloadable for free HERE.

Musical production, scratch, mix and mastering have been done by Brainiac Beats aka El Cerebro, except Praise featuring Joell Ortiz’s track, mixed by the well known Spanish mixing engineer Jorge Gascón.

Diego L Rodriguez is the mastermind behind the artwork.

Hard sound with NY essence and that universal touch that Brainiac Beats always delivers.

What are you waiting for to enjoy this belated Christmas present? Download it now!

description:
Music by Luigi Boccherini 1743-1805 "Menuett" 

had been sung by the "Comedian Harmonists" 5 voices+piano 

7 tracks a cappella, sung and produced by Andreas Herrmann
lyrics
Nein ja nein ja nein ja nein ja nein - ja 

Lieselotte, lass uns auf die Wiese geh'n 
Lieselotte, lass uns in die Zukunft seh'n 
und die Margarithen 
auf der Wiese bitten 
uns zu sagen, wie wird's weitergeh'n. 

Lieselotte, lass uns auf die Wiese geh'n 
was die Blumen sagen wollen wir versteh'n 
noch ist alles offen 
und wir dürfen hoffen, 
dass die Träume in Erfüllung geh'n. 

Bitte glaube mir doch 
niemals irrten sie noch 
und seit vielen Tagen 
quälen mich schon Fragen. 

Lieselotte, lass uns auf die Wiese geh'n 
Lieselotte komm, lass nicht die Zeit vergeh'n 
so ein Tag wie heute 
der bringt Glück und Freude 
für ein ganzes Leben du wirst seh'n. 

Viele glauben den gold'nen Sternen 
doch ich bin sicher dass das nicht stimmt. 
Andre fragen die bunten Karten, 
welchen Verlauf noch ihr Leben nimmt. 

Der Kaffeesatz soll sehr viel wissen, 
doch ehrlich ich glaube nicht daran, 
denn für mich gibt's nur ein Orakel, 
dem man in jedem Fall glauben kann. 

Lieselotte, lass uns auf die Wiese geh'n 
Lieselotte, lass uns in die Zukunft seh'n 
und die Margarithen 
auf der Wiese bitten 
uns zu sagen, wie wird's weitergeh'n. 

Lieselotte, lass uns auf die Wiese geh'n 
was die Blumen sagen wollen wir versteh'n 
noch ist alles offen 
und wir dürfen hoffen, 
dass die Träume in Erfüllung geh'n. 

Bitte glaube mir doch 
niemals irrten sie noch 
und seit vielen Tagen 
quälen mich schon Fragen. 

Lieselotte, lass uns auf die Wiese geh'n 
Lieselotte komm, lass nicht die Zeit vergeh'n 
so ein Tag wie heute 
der bringt Glück und Freude 
für ein ganzes Leben du wirst seh'n.
credits
from Schellack, track released 15 August 2010 
Sung and produced by Andreas Herrmann 

Picture by Flickr Artist Curnen (CC License)
title: Lieselotte, lass uns auf die Wiese geh'n

description:
Music had been sung by the Comedian Harmonists 5 voices+piano 
6 tracks a cappella, sung and produced by Andreas Herrmann
lyrics
Du passt so gut zu mir wie Zucker zum Kaffee 
Du passt so gut zu mir so wie das A zum B 
Der Gedanke, den du denkst 
ja den selben denk ich längst 
und ich weiß schon früh was Du mir abends schenkst ... 

Du passt so gut zu mir wie Blumenduft zum Mai, 
so wie die Sternennacht zur Liebesträumerei, 
wir verstehn uns wunderbar 
ja wir sind direkt ein Paar, 
ohne dich bin ich die Hälfte, das ist wahr. 

Stundenlang könnt ich dir sagen, wie du zu mir passt, 
dass man uns nicht trennen kann. 
Wen du es so gerne hörst und Zeit für mich noch hast, 
dann fang ich noch einmal an ...
credits
from Schellack, track released 15 August 2010 
Picture by Flickr Artist t.animal 
Vocals and Production: Andreas Herrmann

title: Du passt so gut zu mir wie Zucker zum Kaffee

description:
Spanish Folk
Vocals: Carmen Cano
Instruments and Production: AVoxx / Andreas Herrmann


El vito
Con el vito vito vito
con el vito vito va.
Con el vito vito vito
con el vito vito va.

Yo no quiero que me miren
que me pongo colorá.
Yo no quiero que me miren
que me pongo colorá.

No me mires a la cara 
que me pongo colorá
Yo no quiero que me mires
que me vas a enamorar.

Una malagueña fue a
Sevilla a ver los toros.
Y en la mitad del camino
la cautivaron los moros.

Las solteras son de oro
las casadas son de plata.
Las viuditas son de cobre 
y las viejas de hojalata.

The Vito Dance
With the vito, vito, vito,
With the vito, vito, it goes.
With the vito, vito, vito,
With the vito, vito, it goes.

I don't want them to look at me
For I blush. 
I don't want them to look at me
For I blush.

Don't look straight at my face
For I blush.
I don't want you to look at me
For I'm going to fall in love.

A Malaguean lady went to
Sevilla to see the bulls.
And in the middle of the way
The Moors captured her.

Single ladies are of gold
Married ladies are of silver
The widows are of copper
And the old ones are of tin.
title: El Vito

description:
My take on Calendargirl's vocals for August. The horns could possibly benefit from a bit more variation. Having them played with real instruments would work better as well, the current ones sound a bit plastic here and there.

For more details about Calendargirl's project, go check out her website at http://www.calendarsongs.com/
title: el-B & Calendargirl - August (Reggae Rework)
